body:
I do have a system of n equations with m variables where m > n with integer coefficients. I wish to find a set of integer solutions to this system (In my case n = 2 and m = 4). Could somebody tell me how I can do it? I already solved this system with Mathematica but I would like to redo these calculations by hand to understand how their were obtained. The system is:
$\left\{
\begin{array}{l l}
4u - 3v + 4w + 3z = 1\\
-4v - 3u - 4z + 3w = 0
\end{array} \right.$

Given the following system of differential equations \begin{align}
\frac{dy}{dt} &= x
\\ \\
\frac{dx}{dt} &= y
\end{align} is the following operation allowed? \begin{align}
\frac{\dfrac{dy}{dt}}{\dfrac{dx}{dt}}  &= \frac{x}{y}
\\\\
\frac{dy}{dx} &= \frac{x}{y}
\end{align}
